  "investment_thesis": [
    "1. Vision2029 Mid-term Plan: FY29/3 targets of JPY35bn rev / JPY5.25bn OP imply +9.7% revenue CAGR and OPM expansion 14.4%->15.0%. Customer Business +8.9% CAGR is the biggest about-face vs FY26's -3.0% decline.",
    "2. Defense/Space Tech: Vision2029 explicitly elevates 'Space Tech' (small-satellite GNSS systems) to a strategic pillar within Industrial Tech. 4-layer moat (proprietary receiver + QZSS auth + security clearance + space heritage) intact.",
    "3. Stock Business Pivot: Stock revenue mix targeted to grow 7%->20% over 3 years (JPY1.7bn -> JPY7.0bn, 4x). This drives OPM expansion across all segments and structurally improves earnings quality."
  ],
  "key_risks": [
    "1. Customer Business growth pivot from -3% FY26 actual to +8.9% CAGR target is the most aggressive turnaround in the plan; execution risk is highest here.",
    "2. Stock business 4x scale-up requires sales-model transformation (one-shot SI -> recurring services); transition could pressure near-term revenue recognition.",
    "3. Market reaction post-plan (5/9 close ~JPY2,006, +0.0% from pre-plan) suggests investors are skeptical of plan execution. Implied alpha remains deeply pessimistic."
  ],
